headline: Stock Seasonality 2026: The Exact Days to Buy and Sell
summary: Editor’s Note: When the world feels chaotic, investors often assume markets must be too – unpredictable and hostage to every headline. But my colleague Keith Kaplan, CEO of TradeSmith, has spent years proving the opposite. Beneath the noise, he’s discovered remarkably consistent patterns: specific calendar windows when individual stocks have historically risen or fallen, with surprising regularity.
